Now, iper has added an extra element ("Towards the developer space")
here NOT to the header but to the layout two itself, which ruins the
layout. Setting positions absolute for side and main here overrides
flex, but it also means that side and manin need to be defined
precisely so that override does not happen anywhere else */


.v2 .layout.two > .side[style="float:left;width:170px;margin-right:50px"] { /* Side pane */
	min-width: 180px !important;
	margin-right: 10px !important;
}

.v2 .layout.two > .side > .howtotoc#toc > dt > a { /* Api menu items on the left */
	background-color: #393939 !important;
}

.v2 .layout.two > .side > .howtotoc#toc > dt > a:hover { /* Api menu items hovered */
	filter: brightness(120%) !important;
}

.v2 .layout.two > .side > .howtotoc#toc > dt > strong { /* Active api menu item */
	color: #bbb !important;
}

